sentences: Bruno Martino (11 November 1925 – 12 June 2000) was an Italian composer, singer, and pianist.
A Jazz fan, he spent the early years of his career performing with European radio and night club orchestras.
A Jazz fan, he spent the early years of his career performing with European radio and night club orchestras.

Internationally he is best known for his 1960 song Estate, a standard that has been performed by many jazz musicians and singers since the early 1960s, including João Gilberto, Joe Diorio, Chet Baker, Toots Thielemans, Shirley Horn, Eliane Elias, Michel Petrucciani, Monty Alexander, Mike Stern, John Pizzarelli and Robert Jospé.

Martino's hit-song Dracula Cha Cha (later also called Dracula Cha Cha Cha) was first heard in the Italian horror-comedy film Tempi duri per i vampiri (1959) and on a vinyl single released the same year.
